tweets.text:
Alright, thanks to @adam_keesling for the "food" suggestion. 

1 opinion per like! https://t.co/uDxvUkQmBW

@adam_keesling The specific diet you follow is probably less important than the quality of the food in it. 

E.g. a super well sourced vegan diet would probably be healthier than a paleo diet eating mcdonalds meat

@adam_keesling Chicken is a bad food to eat. 

Extremely high suffering :: meat ratio, lower nutritional value than other meats, higher contamination risk in the US.

@adam_keesling No one gets fat from eating fruit. 

The anti-fruit fad from the paleo and Tim Ferriss community is silly.
Most diets are about group signaling as much as health
Meat is going to become a luxury good again over the next ~20 years. McDonalds quality meat will be replaced by fake meats
Fake meats like Beyond and Impossible are absolute garbage and no parent should give it to their children.
Highly processed vegetable oils are *probably* not great for us, but they're really hard to get away from. Especially in restaurants.
Everyone who eats meat should harvest an animal at least once in their life.
Brussel Sprouts get the worst rap as a vegetable, especially as a kid, but they're incredible when cooked right
We still don't understand nutrition or food, so attempts to replace it with things like Soylent are doomed to fail
Diet quality definitely has an impact on mental health
People pointing to the Maasai, Inuit, as examples of how certain diets can be perfectly healthy are being silly. Especially the carnivore crowd.
A carnivore diet seems to help with autoimmune issues, but if you don't have one, you shouldn't be on it.
Dogs' diet evolved alongside developments in agriculture and they're used to eating some grain. Grain free dog food isn't necessarily better for them.

I guess I should be counting. 

16/ You can find studies to support, and discredit, any diet. Pointing to one food study as an argument is intellectually lazy.

17/ Keto can absolutely help with autoimmune issues. 

@cosetteeliason went on one for ~1 month and her eczema hasn't come back 2 years later.
@cosetteeliason 18/ Easy food delivery is probably making us more lonely. By making it easier to eat at home, we socialize less.
@cosetteeliason 19/ Everyone should do a 3-5+ day water-only fast at some point, just to show yourself you can do it. It's not that hard, and it changes your relationship with food.

@cosetteeliason 20/ It's fun to hate on fossil fuels but we couldn't have all the food in the world right now without them. 

Pollution and climate change may be / have been a necessary consequence of global population growth.
@cosetteeliason 21/ Salt isn't bad for you.
@cosetteeliason 22/ Doing a keto diet by eating tons of butter and cream isn't good for you.
@cosetteeliason 23/ But doing a keto diet using good balanced food sources can be very good for you, and is an incredible tool for weight loss.
@cosetteeliason 24/ Juice cleanses are nonsense
@cosetteeliason 25/ What you *don't* eat might be more important than what you *do* eat.
@cosetteeliason 26/ No food or diet blog is fully trustworthy, you need to do your own research.
@cosetteeliason 27/ Definitely no food documentaries are reliable sources of information, they're all based on some agenda and don't go through any kind of peer review / fact checking
